# ProjectFlo — Refactoring Safety

- **Missing file / broken import (blocking):** if an error indicates a missing file/module that existed before, do not guess whether to restore or remove references—get explicit direction (except for clearly dead/no-op imports).
- Use `refactoring-safety.instructions.md` as the canonical refactor gate when doing any structural refactor:
  - read `.github/copilot-instructions.md` and relevant instruction docs
  - baseline tests before edits
  - refactor checklist (target path, files to keep/delete/archive, contracts to verify)
  - after: `pnpm test`, `pnpm build`, `pnpm lint:fix` (when refactor validation is required)
- **Zero backward compatibility:** no shims, no re-export proxies, no dual-path fallbacks; update all consumers in the same change.
- After moves/renames: search for old paths and remove all references; do not leave compatibility barrels.
- When changing DB columns/DTO shapes/service signatures: sweep all callers (services, DTOs, seeds, scripts, frontend bindings) in the same change.
- Prefer deleting stale/duplicate code; move valid-but-unreferenced code to feature `_archive/` only when it’s genuinely correct and intentionally inactive.

